{"title":"Strava mobile updates help us train better inside, stay motivated & keep up with friends","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/23/strava-mobile-updates-help-us-train-better-inside-stay-motivated-keep-up-with-friends/","date":1616507135000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Strava has been trickling out several mobile app functional updates over the past month or so, helping to keep us all motivated and looking forward to training goals ahead. From making it easier to see where friends are riding to seeing how far you’ve come on your own, this series of app updates are helping up stay connected and looking forward to a time when we can ride more together.</p><h2>Strava mobile app updates better connect training &amp; motivation</h2><p>One of the most subtle updates even slipped in under our noses, simply listing the activity location right next to the time stamp for each entry that comes across our feed. Obviously, the location was already there on the map, but now it’s easier at a glimpse to see where your friends were riding, especially nice since many of us still aren’t riding together as much we’d like these days.</p><h3>Strava mobile Monthly Recaps</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review.jpg\" alt=\"Strava mobile app training updates Monthly Recap\" width=\"1800\" height=\"725\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review.jpg 1800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-297x120.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-800x322.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-120x48.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-768x309.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-1536x619.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-696x280.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-1068x430.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-1043x420.jpg 1043w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review.jpg 1800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-297x120.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-800x322.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-120x48.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-768x309.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-1536x619.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-696x280.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-1068x430.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091424/Strava-Monthly-Recap-stats-review-1043x420.jpg 1043w\"></a></p><p>Another one that popped up about a week ago, new Monthly Recaps in your Profile tab gives you a quick personalized overview of your activities for the previous month, showing how it compares to the previous year, plus a day-by-day breakdown of activities by sport. On top of that, paying subscribers also get a more-detailed look breaking down the percentages of their cross-training, a highlight of their longest effort of the last month, and then even a glimpse of what you were doing a year ago.</p><p>Strava says the recap is about looking back to stay motivated for what’s to come. And each element in the Monthly Recap can be shared with friends on Strava, through pretty much any social media platforms, or DM’ed directly to your friends.</p><h3>Indoor training with heart rate, but without GPS</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording.jpg\" alt=\"Strava mobile app training updates, indoor heart rate without GPS\" width=\"800\" height=\"550\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-297x204.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-120x83.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-768x528.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-218x150.jpg 218w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-696x479.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-611x420.jpg 611w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-100x70.jpg 100w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-297x204.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-120x83.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-768x528.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-218x150.jpg 218w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-696x479.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-611x420.jpg 611w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/23091412/Strava-indoor-activity-heart-rate-recording-100x70.jpg 100w\"></a></p><p>Next update up, Strava now lets you record indoor activities that don’t have GPS or accumulated movement distances directly from your smartphone via the iOS or Android app. Now, for example: yoga, weight training, cross-fit, or even aerobics activities can be recorded with heart rate data logged as well. Your indoor activities track start time, elapsed time, and heart rate data (if you have a heart rate monitor paired to the phone), plus showing you calories burned after the fact.</p><h3>Improved mobile activity search</h3><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Strava-mobile-activity-search-update_train-better.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Strava-mobile-activity-search-update_train-better.jpg\" alt=\"Strava mobile training app update, activity search\" width=\"1500\" height=\"945\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Strava-mobile-activity-search-update_train-better.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com